The crisis in the APC is deepening as a faction of the party in Ekiti has suspended Governor Fayemi. Fayemi was accused of working Obaseki and the PDP in the just concluded Edo election, among other allegations. The APC in Ekiti state said it suspended the Governor for alleged anti-party activities. Among other allegations, Fayemi was accused of working against the APC in the just concluded Edo governorship election. The state APC claimed Fayemi was conniving with the PDP in a bid to secure the party’s vice-presidential ticket in 2023.